🔐 Admin Authentication Plan – KaviCakes Order Management System
1️⃣ Hard-coded credentials ❌ (NOT recommended)

Do NOT hard-code admin username/password in the system.

Why it’s bad:

Password is exposed in source code

Cannot change password without code changes

Fails security best practices

Panel members usually deduct marks for this

✅ Correct approach:
Store admin credentials in the database with proper hashing.

2️⃣ Admin Registration (One-Time Setup) ✅

Since there is only ONE admin, registration must be controlled, not open like customer signup.

✔ Corrected Plan:

Admin registration happens only once

After registration:

No new admins can register

System blocks additional admin signups

Registration Flow:

Admin enters:

Email

Password

Confirm password

System validates:

Email format is valid

Password meets security rules

System checks:

Admin table is empty

If admin already exists → block registration

Password is:

Hashed (e.g., bcrypt)

Stored in database

OTP sent to admin email

Admin enters OTP

OTP verified

Admin account status = ACTIVE

📌 Improvement:
Add is_verified = true/false field in admin table.

3️⃣ Admin Login (Sign In) 🔑
Login Flow:

Admin enters:

Email

Password

System checks:

Email exists in admin table

Password hash matches

Account status = ACTIVE

If valid:

Generate JWT token (role = ADMIN)

Token is:

Stored securely (HTTP-only cookie / local storage)

Sent with every admin API request

📌 System Check:
Before accessing admin pages → system checks is admin logged in.

4️⃣ Admin Route Protection 🛡️

All admin APIs and pages must be protected.

Validation Rules:

JWT must exist

Token must be valid

Token role must be ADMIN

Token must not be expired

❌ Customers cannot access admin routes
❌ Direct URL access is blocked

5️⃣ Forgot Password (Improved Plan) 🔁

Your idea is correct, just needs refinement.

Password Reset Flow:

Admin clicks Forgot Password

Admin enters registered email

System checks:

Email exists

Account is ACTIVE

System generates:

One-time reset token (time-limited)

Password reset link sent to admin email

Admin opens link

Admin enters:

New password

Confirm password

System:

Hashes new password

Updates database

Invalidates reset token

📌 Same flow as customer side (good consistency)

6️⃣ Admin Password Change (While Logged In) 🔄

Strongly recommended improvement

Flow:

Admin enters:

Current password

New password

System validates:

Current password matches DB

New password rules satisfied

System updates:

New hashed password in DB

Admin remains logged in (or forced re-login)

7️⃣ OTP & Email Security Enhancements ✉️
OTP Rules:

OTP expires after 5–10 minutes

Maximum retry attempts (e.g., 3)

OTP stored temporarily (hashed)

8️⃣ Admin Table Structure (Suggested) 🗄️
Admin
- admin_id
- email
- password_hash
- is_verified
- status (ACTIVE / INACTIVE)
- created_at
- updated_at

